# ============================================================================
# Environment Variables — WINOVYA Intelligence Platform
# ============================================================================
# Copy to .env.local (dev) or configure in Netlify UI (production)
# ============================================================================

# SUPABASE — Backend Database & Edge Functions
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# SUPABASE — Development & Deployments (GitHub Actions)
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=sbp_xxxxxxxxxxxx  # Personal access token
SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD=your-db-password

# SUPABASE — Service Role (Edge Functions with full privileges)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# VITE — Frontend environment
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_ENVIRONMENT=development  # development, preview, production

# GITHUB ACTIONS — For CI/CD Workflows
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxx  # Personal access token with repo access

# NETLIFY — Hosting & CI/CD
NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN=nflytxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx  # Personal access token
NETLIFY_SITE_ID=your-site-name.netlify.app

# ============================================================================
# HOW TO GET THESE VALUES
# ============================================================================

# VITE_SUPABASE_URL + VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY:
#   1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
#   2. Select your project
#   3. Settings → API
#   4. Copy "Project URL" (VITE_SUPABASE_URL)
#   5. Copy "anon public" key (VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY)

# SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN:
#   1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens
#   2. Create "Personal API token"
#   3. Copy the full token

# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY:
#   1. Go to your Supabase project
#   2. Settings → API
#   3. Copy "service_role secret" key (FULL PERMISSIONS - keep secret!)

# SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD:
#   Your database password from project setup
#   (Store in GitHub Secrets, NEVER commit to repo)

# NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN:
#   1. Go to https://app.netlify.com/user/applications
#   2. New access token
#   3. Copy the token

# NETLIFY_SITE_ID:
#   1. Go to your Netlify site
#   2. Site settings → General
#   3. Copy "Site ID"

# ============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================================================
# ⚠️  NEVER commit .env.local to git (it's in .gitignore)
# ⚠️  NEVER share SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN or SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
# ⚠️  Use GitHub Secrets for CI/CD (not repo environment variables)
# ⚠️  Rotate tokens regularly (especially SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY)
# ✓  VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY is fine in frontend (limited permissions)

# ============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOW
# ============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Fill in your actual values from Supabase/GitHub/Netlify
# 3. Run: npm run dev
# 4. Frontend loads env vars via VITE_ prefix (client-side safe only)

# ============================================================================
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT
# ============================================================================
# 1. Configure in Netlify UI: Site settings → Build & deploy → Environment
#    Add: VITE_SUPABASE_URL, VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, VITE_API_BASE_URL
# 2. Configure in GitHub: Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
#    Add: SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN, SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD, etc.
# 3. Deploy: git push origin main (auto-triggers GitHub Actions + Netlify)

# ============================================================================
